+summaryLines.push("Overall conclusions: the strongest treatment signal was for palbociclib, with an additional positive interaction in ER-positive disease and a negative interaction in PIK3CA-mutated disease. Tamoxifen, trastuzumab, olaparib, sacituzumab govitecan, and pembrolizumab did not show convincing adjusted main-effect benefits in this specification. Disease burden and host-state markers were clearer: ECOG performance status, stage IV disease, brain metastases, weight loss, high LDH, and higher Ki-67 were adverse, while higher albumin and ER positivity were favorable. Several clinically plausible treatment-biomarker hypotheses were refuted or not supported, including tamoxifen by ER status, trastuzumab by HER2 status/amplification, olaparib by BRCA1/2 mutation, sacituzumab by triple-negative status, and pembrolizumab by autoimmune disease; pembrolizumab in triple-negative disease showed a small significant negative interaction rather than the hypothesized larger benefit.");
